&lt;h1 id="index-of-refraction-measurements"&gt;Index of Refraction Measurements&lt;a class="anchor" href="#index-of-refraction-measurements"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The refractive index is defined as the speed of light (in vacuum) over the phase velocity \( n = \frac{c}{v_{\phi}} \), \( v_\phi = \omega / k \). Recall that in vacuum the phase velocity is just the speed of light (\( n = 1 \) in vacuum). In a plasma, we know that the dispersion relation will be substantially different.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Spectroscopic Measurements</title><link>https://peppyhare.github.io/r/notes/UWAA560/06-spectroscopic-measurements/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://peppyhare.github.io/r/notes/UWAA560/06-spectroscopic-measurements/</guid><description>&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://peppyhare.github.io/r/katex/katex.min.css" /&gt;
