&lt;h1 id="zeeman-spectroscopy"&gt;Zeeman Spectroscopy&lt;a class="anchor" href="#zeeman-spectroscopy"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="motivation"&gt;Motivation&lt;a class="anchor" href="#motivation"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In high-energy-density plasmas, the current density distribution is strongly tied to the magnetic field distribution, and in some regions measurement of the B-field is the only way to obtain current density measurements. The magnetic field also determines resistivity, plasma dynamics, and energy balance.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>